name: shed construction, large, wood, non-insulated, fire-unprotected | shed, large, wood, non-insulated, fire-unprotected | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/15474/documentation

This global dataset is a copy of the regional CH dataset, except for the following modifications.;The production volume represents the global annual production.;The geographicalCorrelation score of every pedigree matrix of was changed to '5'.;The comments below were part of the CH regional dataset.;This dataset represents the construction material of 1 m2 useable surface of a not flame resistant shed, not to be used as a garage for motor vehicles. ;Features of the model used: Building volume: 1478 m3; Useable space: 264 m2; Service life span: 50 years. Fire-unprotected: Ceiling with flammable material, thus not to be used as a garage for combustion engine; non-insulated: simple construction of wooden walls without insulation material; light basement with concrete.;This dataset refers to an average situation; for specific situations exchanges might differ substantially due to site specific parameters. 

The activity starts with the construction of the building.

Elements included are: 3-sided closed shed, not flame-resistant, concrete floor, non insulated wood construction. Not included: flame-resistant garage component. The activity ends with the disposal of the building material.
category: F:Construction/41:Construction of buildings/410:Construction of buildings/4100:Construction of buildings

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The calculation of the construction materials employed is based on Agroscope PBK+  (Modular Construction Standards for Farm Building Costs +) System (Dux 2004). Based on construction variants for model buildings, the necessary building materials for construction, repair and replacement are calculated with the aid of the PBK+ database. In addition, the consumption of energy and auxiliary materials during operation of the building can be determined.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The amount of the exchanges are copy from a regional dataset.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: This process is identical with the SALCA-process 'Shed, large, wood, non-insulated, fire-unprotected, at farm/m2/CH/I U' excluding land occupation and transformation processes .
